.TH "ice_bridge_setlink" 9 "ice_bridge_setlink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_bridge_setlink \- Set the hardware bridge mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_bridge_setlink
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct nlmsghdr *nlh "  ","
.BI "u16 __always_unused flags "  ","
.BI "struct netlink_ext_ack __always_unused *extack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the netdev being configured
.IP "nlh" 12
RTNL message
.IP "flags" 12
bridge setlink flags
.IP "extack" 12
netlink extended ack
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets the bridge mode (VEB/VEPA) of the switch to which the netdev (VSI) is
hooked up to. Iterates through the PF VSI list and sets the loopback mode (if
not already set for all VSIs connected to this switch. And also update the
unicast switch filter rules for the corresponding switch of the netdev.
